AGI - They were seized by the Carabinieri 1800 marijuana plants, denouncing two people free of charge.
&nbsp;
The operation began in the Rosalì fraction of Reggio Calabria, during a control aimed at the repression of the abusive laces to the electricity network >, carried out by the Carabinieri of the local station with the support of specialized personnel. During the service, the military discovered an abusive link feeding an agricultural shed.
&nbsp;
Unsatisfied by the situation, they deepened control and within the structure they found a vast cultivation of marijuana, > with a sophisticated lighting system > and ventilation to promote the growth of plants. The two owners stated that it was sativa cannabis intended for the market of the so-called “cannabis light”, but the subsequent investigations showed the opposite.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
In order to verify the lawfulness of cultivation, the soldiers of the Carabinieri Forestali Group of Reggio Calabria were activated, > who carried out withdrawals and sampling of the substance >. The samples taken were tested at the laboratories of the Mediterranean University of Reggio Calabria, which detected a THC value higher than the limits of law. This confirmed that the substance found was drug addict.
<br> Ensure the illicit nature of the plantation, the soldiers have been seized by the entire production plant.> Three greenhouses were found inside the shed containing a total of 1800 plants> in different stages of growth. In addition, a room used as a grow room, equipped with halogen lamps, fans, timers and thermal carpets to ensure optimal conditions for cultivation. In addition to the plantation, sixteen bags containing already dried and ready-to-market marijuana have been seized for a total weight of more than 170 kilograms.
<br The two owners of the structure were arrested for theft of electricity, > having made an abusive connection to feed the cultivation plant. In addition, they have been deferred into a state of freedom for the crime of illicit cultivation and detention of narcotic substances. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> Collaboration with the University
The key element for the success of the operation was the collaboration between the Carabinieri and the Mediterranean University of Reggio Calabria. Thanks to an agreement signed in March 2022, a research and control programme was launched on the legal cannabis chain, > with particular attention to the verification of THC content. This synergy allows to ensure greater control of the sector and to quickly identify any violations of current legislation.
<br <br> &nbsp;
&nbsp;
